        "description": "Register - Create a new user account\n\nPurpose\n- This endpoint creates a new user account in the system. It accepts a JSON payload with the user's name, email, and password, validates the input, and returns the created user's data and an authentication token on success.\n\nRequest URL\n- POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/register\n\nRequest body (JSON) - required fields\n- name (string): The full name of the user. Validation: required, minimum 2 characters, maximum 100 characters.\n- email (string): The user's email address. Validation: required, must be a valid email format, unique in the system.\n- password (string): The account password. Validation: required, minimum 6 characters (recommend 8+), should include letters and numbers for stronger security.\n\nExample request body\n{\n  \"name\": \"Test User\",\n  \"email\": \"test@mail.com\",\n  \"password\": \"123456\"\n}\n\nSuccessful response\n- Status: 201 Created\n- Example JSON body:\n{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"data\": {\n    \"id\": \"<user-id>\",\n    \"name\": \"Test User\",\n    \"email\": \"test@mail.com\"\n  },\n  \"token\": \"<jwt-token>\"\n}\n\nCommon error responses\n- 400 Bad Request: Validation errors. Response typically contains details about which fields failed validation (e.g., missing name, invalid email format, password too short).\n- 409 Conflict: Email already exists. Sent when the provided email is already registered.\n- 500 Internal Server Error: Unexpected server error. Check server logs for details.\n\nTesting notes\n- Run the API server locally and ensure it listens on http://localhost:5000.\n- In Postman, use the active environment or create an environment variable for the base URL, e.g., BASE_URL = http://localhost:5000 and set the request URL to {{BASE_URL}}/api/auth/register if you prefer using environments.\n- Set the request body to raw -> JSON and paste the example JSON above. Send the POST request and check for a 201 response and returned token.\n\nLinks\n- Collection: [My Collection](collection/52303654-7a3730d5-a492-4c66-8bf1-ed0506f369fe)\n- Request: [Register](request/52303654-37c5397a-1307-41ad-a664-4d7aeac2503a)\n\nQuick checklist to test\n- Ensure local server is running at http://localhost:5000\n- (Optional) Set environment variable: BASE_URL = http://localhost:5000\n- Use POST {{BASE_URL}}/api/auth/register or POST http://localhost:5000/api/auth/register\n- Body: raw JSON with name, email, password\n- Expect 201 Created and a JSON response with user data and token"
      },
